		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Very nice, another cart saved ~<br /><br />I wouldn't bother at all with SRAM, the FeRAM is better though it has limited writes durability but you do get unused part of the chip only top address line change away.<br />EDIT: fixed stuff. I looked at my old research and there's 320 bytes of save data actually used in Sonic3 alone, rest in S3&amp;K.<br /><img src="http://www.tmeeco.eu/BitShit/S3SRAM.png" alt="Image" />

		

